 it's something that is so refreshing,

44
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:09,700
 but it's also something that is anointed.

45
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:11,120
 It's a gift.

46
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:15,400
 And so, Father, I pray as she shares that gift with us today

47
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:18,800
 we would truly lean in, receive it,

48
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,560
 and do something with it.

49
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:22,800
 In Jesus' name, amen.

50
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:23,640
 - Amen.

51
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:29,040
 What a weekend we've had, and incredible.

52
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:32,380
 I feel like my friend who, whenever he's done eating a meal,

53
00:02:32,380 --> 00:02:34,560
 he pushes back from the table and he goes,

54
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:37,060
 "Is it supposed to hurt when you're done eating?"

55
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:38,200
 (laughing)

56
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,280
 Right?

57
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,840
 I feel like that kind of weekend where it's just like,

58
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:42,360
 "Could there be more?"

59
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:46,180
 And then the answer, of course, is yes, there's more.

60
00:02:46,180 --> 00:02:47,020
 There's more.

61
00:02:47,020 --> 00:02:52,100
 And our task here is to increase our capacity, right?

62
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:53,680
 It's not that there's more of God,

63
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,800
 it's that there's more room in us

64
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:58,880
 for the God who fills us in every way.

65
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:02,160
 And I still remember the day that my eldest son

66
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:05,160
 went to first day of school, kindergarten.

67
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:07,920
 And I was living in Australia at the time,

68
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,640
 and so he was about five,

69
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:11,800
 and he wanted to walk by himself even,

70
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,280
 you know, like I couldn't hold his hand.

71
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:16,000
 He was like all independent, went to school first day.

72
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,040
 And it was quite a day, and when he got home,

73
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,820
 I was all excited, and I said to him, you know,

74
00:03:19,820 --> 00:03:20,920
 "How did it go, you know,

75
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:23,320
 "your first day of kindergarten in Australia?"

76
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:25,560
 I mean, like, "Come on, how was it?"

77
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,200
 And he said, "It was boring."

78
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:29,080
 (audience laughing)

79
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:31,240
 I was like, "How could it be boring?"

80
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:33,060
 And he said, "Well, all we did today

81
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:35,680
 "was we just literally took turns telling stories

82
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:39,440
 "about what we had done over the summer break."

83
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:41,560
 And I said, "That doesn't sound boring.

84
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:44,000
 "Like, we did some actual cool things over the summer break.

85
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,580
 "I was like, so what did you share?

86
00:03:46,580 --> 00:03:47,680
 "Like, what was your story?"

87
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:51,540
 And he said, "Well, I wanted mine to be really good,

88
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:53,160
 "so I made one up."

89
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:55,880
 (audience laughing)

90
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:57,760
 And I said, "Really?"

91
00:03:57,760 --> 00:04:00,120
 Out of spot of preacher's kid.

92
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:02,240
 So I said, "Well, what did you say?"

93
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:04,840
 And he goes, "Well, Mom, you remember that time

94
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:08,620
 "back in Canada when I was in that go-kart race,

95
00:04:08,620 --> 00:04:10,280
 "and I was going around the track,

96
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,880
 "and then all of a sudden my go-kart,

97
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:15,300
 "it like exploded and it turned into a motorcycle,

98
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:17,660
 "and then I ran that motorcycle all the way through,

99
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:20,720
 "and I won, and they gave me that big gold trophy?"

100
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,620
 And I said, "Nope."

101
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:23,700
 (audience laughing)

102
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:25,460
 "Don't remember."

103
00:04:25,460 --> 00:04:26,500
 And then he just looked at me,

104
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,420
 and he put his hand on my head like this,

105
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:30,240
 and he just closed his eyes.

106
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:33,740
 And then he said, "Do you remember now?"

107
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:36,740
 (audience laughing)

108
00:04:36,740 --> 00:04:39,660
 My son, his name is Zion.

109
00:04:39,660 --> 00:04:43,020
 What he's after is a better story.

110
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:46,660
 He's after a better story.

111
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:48,700
 It's what we're all after.

112
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,780
 You know, actually, sometimes I think

113
00:04:50,780 --> 00:04:52,620
 when we get to heaven, the first day of heaven's

114
00:04:52,620 --> 00:04:54,040
 just gonna be us telling stories

115
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:56,300
 about what we did on our summer break,

116
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:58,000
 and I want mine to be a good one.

117
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,300
 And here's the thing.

118
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:03,700
 I think the way that Jesus invites us to live our lives

119
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:05,460
 is we don't have to make it up.

120
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:08,780
 Our stories will be good, right?

121
00:05:08,780 --> 00:05:09,900
 Our stories will be worthy.

122
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:14,220
 Our stories will be helpful and good and full

123
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:17,340
 of the abundant Zoe life that Jesus offers us

124
00:05:17,340 --> 00:05:18,520
 if we'll live that way.

125
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:23,820
 In some ways, even coming to church together like this

126
00:05:23,820 --> 00:05:25,340
 and worshiping and remembering,

127
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:26,780
 I mean, even that last song of worship

128
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:29,940
 is from a guy who was a prisoner on an island of Patmos,

129
00:05:29,940 --> 00:05:31,540
 like under the boot of the empire.

130
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:33,740
 I mean, literally, like Christians are being persecuted

131
00:05:33,740 --> 00:05:36,740
 everywhere in Rome, and he's mustering up.

132
00:05:36,740 --> 00:05:38,740
 I mean, I can only, it was not anything like that.

133
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:40,540
 He's in a prison cell in the middle of nowhere,

134
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:43,620
 and he's probably just going like, "I sing holy."

135
00:05:43,620 --> 00:05:46,640
 Like he's trying to muster up his own sense of self,

136
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:49,260
 and he says, "I'm worshiping on the Lord's day

137
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:51,780
 "as a prisoner," and then all of a sudden,

138
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:55,540
 I hear this voice from heaven, like a trumpet,

139
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:57,780
 and it says, "Come on up here.

140
00:05:57,780 --> 00:06:00,420
 "Come up here, I wanna show you some things.

141
00:06:00,420 --> 00:06:02,420
 "I wanna tell you some things.

142
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:04,840
 "I wanna tell you some things that are more real

143
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:06,620
 "than the real you're experiencing right now,

144
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:09,820
 "that are more true, that they're the character of God,

145
00:06:09,820 --> 00:06:12,360
 "the invitation that God has for all of his children

146
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,320
 "to be beloved, to be known.

147
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,900
 "You know, come up here, come up now."

148
00:06:16,940 --> 00:06:19,580
 And all the angels cry, "Holy."

149
00:06:19,580 --> 00:06:23,060
 And this is sort of this resetting, this invitation.

150
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:25,660
 I wanna take a look at the life of the disciples

151
00:06:25,660 --> 00:06:27,700
 in Mark chapter four, just really quick,

152
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:30,420
 just like a little story that's kinda set

153
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:32,260
 in the life of Jesus and the disciples,

154
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:34,540
 that is this one more, you know,

155
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:36,260
 in this rhythm that Jesus has,

156
00:06:36,260 --> 00:06:39,980
 where he's always inviting people to come, come and see.

157
00:06:39,980 --> 00:06:41,940
 And this is one of the great problems

158
00:06:41,940 --> 00:06:45,300
 that we have sometimes in our faith journey

159
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:49,620
 in Christianity is somehow we've come under this idea

160
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:51,980
 that is an illusion, that Christianity

161
00:06:51,980 --> 00:06:53,740
 is about what we believe.

162
00:06:53,740 --> 00:06:55,860
 You know, there's just a construct,

163
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:57,260
 there's just another religion,

164
00:06:57,260 --> 00:06:58,860
 there's just a construct of belief.

165
00:06:58,860 --> 00:07:00,820
 And so we say, like, if we believe these things,

166
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:03,460
 or if I hold to these things, then that's what this is.

167
00:07:03,460 --> 00:07:05,660
 It's just like a practice of another religion.

168
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:08,820
 But it's not, it's not, that's an illusion.

169
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:12,100
 The real thing, like the real faith practice

170
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:15,620
 is an invitation to actually follow Jesus.

171
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:19,700
 It's an invitation to come, to see, to taste, to move.

172
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:22,380
 The invitation to follow Jesus

173
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:25,980
 is always a disruption to status quo.

174
00:07:25,980 --> 00:07:28,700
 And an invitation into growth and a reality

175
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:31,100
 to experience something that is beyond

176
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:34,940
 what we could even ever conjure up in our best stories.

177
00:07:34,940 --> 00:07:36,100
 And so this is one of those,

178
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:37,900
 this is like a little tiny snapshot

179
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:39,580
 in the life of Jesus and the disciples

180
00:07:39,580 --> 00:07:44,220
 that I think holds some keys to this disruptive reimagining

181
00:07:44,220 --> 00:07:46,740
 of what our faith is and what it means to follow Jesus.

182
00:07:46,740 --> 00:07:50,660
 And it's in Mark's Gospel, chapter four, and near the end.

183
00:07:50,660 --> 00:07:51,700
 We're all gonna read it together.

184
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:54,420
 I'm just gonna invite you to read it out loud with me.

185
00:07:54,420 --> 00:07:55,540
 Are you ready?

186
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:58,140
 Here we go, Mark chapter four, starting at verse 35,

187
00:07:58,140 --> 00:07:59,420
 and let's go.

188
00:07:59,420 --> 00:08:03,640
 "That day, when evening came, he said to his disciples,

189
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:06,300
 "let us go over to the other side.

190
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:08,040
 "And leaving the crowd behind,

191
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:11,720
 "they took him along just as he was in the boat.

192
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:14,080
 "There were also other boats with him.

193
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:16,220
 "A furious squall came up,

194
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:18,260
 "and the waves broke over the boat

195
00:08:18,260 --> 00:08:20,560
 "so that it was nearly swamped.

196
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:23,780
 "Jesus was in the stern, sleeping on a cushion.

197
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:26,440
 "And the disciples woke him and said to him,

198
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:29,660
 "Teacher, don't you care if we drown?

199
00:08:29,660 --> 00:08:33,340
 "He got up, rebuked the wind, and said to the waves,

200
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:35,500
 "Quiet, be still.

201
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:39,080
 "Then the wind died down, and it was completely calm.

202
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:42,800
 "He said to his disciples, why are you so afraid?

203
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:44,880
 "Do you still have no faith?

204
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:47,620
 "They were terrified and asked each other,

205
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:48,920
 "Who is this?

206
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:52,200
 "Even the wind and the waves obey him."

207
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,020
 Amen.

208
00:08:53,020 --> 00:08:56,460
 This invitation that Jesus gives to the disciples

209
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:59,020
 in this context is a disruption.

210
00:08:59,020 --> 00:09:03,240
 And it's a disruption because, number one,

211
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,200
 they're killing it.

212
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,260
 They're doing amazing.

213
00:09:06,260 --> 00:09:09,640
 Like, if you read a little bit before this,

214
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:11,440
 you'll see they're in the, you know,

215
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,840
 Jesus is killing it in mystery.

216
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,040
 He's just like, he's winning.

217
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:16,360
 You know, there's crowds of people, he's healing everybody.

218
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:18,240
 People are being healed of diseases

219
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,520
 and cured of evil spirits,

220
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:21,440
 and they're just like, whispers are going everywhere.

221
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,280
 This is probably the one who was expected.

222
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:24,720
 You know, this is probably the Messiah.

223
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:26,260
 There's all these, I mean, the disciples

224
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:27,960
 are probably just living their best lives.

225
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:29,960
 Their moms are just like, that's my boy over there

226
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,780
 with that rabbi who's healing all the people.

227
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:33,560
 I mean, it's just like, woo-hoo!

228
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:36,080
 And Jesus is like, yeah, we should,

229
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,540
 now's a good time to go.

230
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:40,480
 It's like, no, now's not a good time to go.

231
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,120
 Like, now's a good time to stay,

232
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,020
 'cause if we stay here, we could keep building this thing.

233
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:46,120
 I mean, we could be like the height of success.

234
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,760
 We could be like, the dreams could come true.

235
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:49,680
 My mom could be actually proud of me, you know?

236
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:51,160
 And then Jesus is like, no, let's go.

237
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:53,240
 And when he says, let's go to the other side,

238
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:55,880
 it's not just like, let's go to the other side,

239
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:58,800
 like of the lake, 'cause it's like better over there.

240
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,680
 It's like, let's go to the other side of the tracks.

241
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:04,240
 It's like, let's go to that part of the lake

242
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:06,880
 where your mom said, don't go there,

243
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:09,120
 because over there are all the compromisers.

244
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,840
 Over there are all the pig farmers,

245
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,400
 which if you're Jewish and kosher at all,

246
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,960
 you know that's not what you want to be near.

247
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:17,240
 Over there is where all those Roman sympathizers are,

248
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:19,320
 all those sellouts of the empire.

249
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:22,200
 Over there is where all of those people live.

250
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,440
 Don't go over there.

251
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:26,240
 And in the midst of this successful, amazing ministry,

252
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:29,680
 Jesus says, yeah, we should, you know where we should go?

253
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:33,400
 I remember living in Australia

254
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:35,440
 and I was doing some social justice work there,

255
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:38,600
 trying to help women who were suffering

256
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:42,320
 from sexual exploitation within a brothel system

257
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:43,620
