00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:07,420
 it's, all it is is resistance.

519
00:20:07,420 --> 00:20:08,780
 I mean, Jesus literally, like,

520
00:20:08,780 --> 00:20:10,740
 if only he had a set in the scriptures,

521
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:12,740
 guys, this is gonna be hard.

522
00:20:12,740 --> 00:20:17,060
 Oh, wait a minute, he did.

523
00:20:17,060 --> 00:20:19,940
 Over and over and over, the world's gonna hate you,

524
00:20:19,940 --> 00:20:21,560
 the resistance is gonna be hard,

525
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:23,480
 people might insult you and persecute you

526
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:25,340
 and say all kinds of false things about,

527
00:20:25,340 --> 00:20:26,980
 as the disciples mature in their faith,

528
00:20:26,980 --> 00:20:28,740
 he's like, they're probably even gonna kill you,

529
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:29,920
 but don't worry.

530
00:20:34,140 --> 00:20:37,420
 This is the invitation to be formed by Christ,

531
00:20:37,420 --> 00:20:39,540
 is a disruption to the status quo

532
00:20:39,540 --> 00:20:42,220
 and an invitation to actually follow Jesus

533
00:20:42,220 --> 00:20:45,380
 and be formed by the resistance.

534
00:20:45,380 --> 00:20:47,500
 I don't think the storm that came up on that lake

535
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,100
 was just a happenstance, I don't think,

536
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:51,020
 oh, nuts, Jesus picked the wrong night,

537
00:20:51,020 --> 00:20:52,060
 I don't think anything,

538
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:54,500
 I think the resistance is part of the training.

539
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:58,900
 That's how we learn to be disciples.

540
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:02,380
 The resistance trains us, makes us stronger,

541
00:21:02,380 --> 00:21:04,900
 helps us get to the core of what it is

542
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:06,580
 and who it is that we are to know

543
00:21:06,580 --> 00:21:08,660
 and encounter Jesus for ourselves,

544
00:21:08,660 --> 00:21:10,620
 so that when we actually go and tell the good news,

545
00:21:10,620 --> 00:21:12,340
 we've encountered it,

546
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:16,640
 we know the one of whom we speak, this Jesus.

547
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:19,180
 And so the storm comes against them

548
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:20,940
 and there's four questions in the text

549
00:21:20,940 --> 00:21:22,260
 that I just wanna follow quickly.

550
00:21:22,260 --> 00:21:24,960
 The first one is the disciples' panic.

551
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:27,580
 The disciples are freaking out

552
00:21:27,580 --> 00:21:29,540
 and this must have been a pretty bad storm

553
00:21:29,540 --> 00:21:32,300
 because they go wake up Jesus,

554
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:34,700
 Jesus is sleeping, which is a whole other thing,

555
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:36,780
 Jesus isn't afraid of chaos, by the way.

556
00:21:36,780 --> 00:21:39,740
 Surrender is not trying harder,

557
00:21:39,740 --> 00:21:42,660
 it's relaxing into the goodness of God,

558
00:21:42,660 --> 00:21:44,540
 the grace of God, the strength of God,

559
00:21:44,540 --> 00:21:48,800
 the kingship of God, and Jesus is surrendered to God.

560
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:52,780
 And the disciples wake him up

561
00:21:52,780 --> 00:21:56,460
 and all of the verbs there are like, they're panicked,

562
00:21:56,460 --> 00:21:59,660
 and they say to Jesus this question,

563
00:21:59,660 --> 00:22:03,160
 do you not even care if we drown?

564
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:06,100
 That's a fascinating question.

565
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:09,960
 It's not save us, we're gonna drown,

566
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:13,260
 it's a deeper question than that.

567
00:22:13,260 --> 00:22:15,960
 Teacher, they say,

568
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:21,360
 do you even care if we drown?

569
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:24,860
 You know what that question is?

570
00:22:25,820 --> 00:22:27,260
 That question's honest.

571
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:31,740
 That question is a deeper question

572
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:34,900
 than most people get to in their journey of discipleship.

573
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:38,740
 That question is a question that can only actually be asked

574
00:22:38,740 --> 00:22:41,500
 when times are tough, when fear is there,

575
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:44,120
 when the panic sets in, when you're in an encounter

576
00:22:44,120 --> 00:22:46,120
 that's too hard for you and too difficult to you,

577
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:47,620
 do you even care?

578
00:22:47,620 --> 00:22:50,200
 Do you even care?

579
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:53,740
 I remember journeying with a friend of mine

580
00:22:53,740 --> 00:22:57,940
 who had a life that looked just great.

581
00:22:57,940 --> 00:22:59,540
 She's married to the chief of surgery,

582
00:22:59,540 --> 00:23:03,300
 she was living it, she was wealthy, she was an artist,

583
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:05,620
 she has all these things, she's beautiful.

584
00:23:05,620 --> 00:23:07,260
 But actually the reality of her life

585
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:10,420
 was that her marriage was a mess, her friends weren't real,

586
00:23:10,420 --> 00:23:13,300
 it was all fake, it was like she was isolated,

587
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:15,600
 she was stuck, no one really knew her, no one knew her,

588
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:18,140
 she felt isolated and alone, she was depressed,

589
00:23:18,140 --> 00:23:20,760
 and she just kept taking more and more medication

590
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:22,760
 to try to numb her feelings.

591
00:23:23,580 --> 00:23:25,020
 And I remember saying to her one day,

592
00:23:25,020 --> 00:23:26,620
 I'm not even recognizing you, man,

593
00:23:26,620 --> 00:23:28,860
 how much meds are you taking?

594
00:23:28,860 --> 00:23:32,600
 By the way, if you suffer from clinical depression

595
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,180
 or something like that, I'm a big fan

596
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:36,660
 of getting professional help and finding some medications

597
00:23:36,660 --> 00:23:38,100
 that might help, but this was not that,

598
00:23:38,100 --> 00:23:40,100
 this was like a masking, this was like a covering,

599
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:41,180
 this was a numbing.

600
00:23:41,180 --> 00:23:42,620
 And I said to her, what are you doing?

601
00:23:42,620 --> 00:23:45,100
 She said, Danielle, I don't know what else to do.

602
00:23:45,100 --> 00:23:45,980
 What else am I gonna do?

603
00:23:45,980 --> 00:23:48,020
 I'm just crying all the time.

604
00:23:48,020 --> 00:23:49,820
 What am I gonna say to people when I'm in these places,

605
00:23:49,820 --> 00:23:50,920
 I'm just crying all the time.

606
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:53,420
 I said, I don't know, maybe I'm sad.

607
00:23:54,180 --> 00:23:57,500
 Maybe I'm sad, maybe like get to the place

608
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:59,700
 where instead of covering the stuff and numbing the stuff

609
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:01,700
 and pretending the stuff and getting stuck

610
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:04,580
 in these sort of like pretenses of fineness

611
00:24:04,580 --> 00:24:06,460
 that we actually got honest.

612
00:24:06,460 --> 00:24:10,140
 Do you know that hope can't even be hope

613
00:24:10,140 --> 00:24:12,300
 unless it gets honest?

614
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:13,860
 Do you know the majority of the Psalms

615
00:24:13,860 --> 00:24:16,680
 are just David saying, do you even care?

616
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:21,540
 Do you know it's okay to be honest with God?

617
00:24:21,540 --> 00:24:24,460
 Do you know actually that real and true discipleship

618
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:28,940
 is actually getting to a place where you could be honest

619
00:24:28,940 --> 00:24:31,060
 with your lament, with the brokenness,

620
00:24:31,060 --> 00:24:32,980
 with the condition of your life?

621
00:24:32,980 --> 00:24:36,180
 Had another friend I had, I was playing

622
00:24:36,180 --> 00:24:37,620
 in a woman's basketball league,

623
00:24:37,620 --> 00:24:41,220
 and she was a council woman on the city hall.

624
00:24:41,220 --> 00:24:43,300
 She was running for mayor.

625
00:24:43,300 --> 00:24:45,860
 And I was doing some afterschool stuff with inner city kids.

626
00:24:45,860 --> 00:24:48,420
 And I said to her, I'd really love some help fundraising.

627
00:24:48,420 --> 00:24:49,340
 Do you think you would come?

628
00:24:49,340 --> 00:24:51,060
 I thought this will be good for her image

629
00:24:51,060 --> 00:24:53,580
 and this will be good for our money.

630
00:24:53,580 --> 00:24:55,500
 I said, do you think you could come help me fundraise?

631
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:56,980
 And she said, well, let me come see the program.

632
00:24:56,980 --> 00:24:58,760
 So she came, I showed her around, she loved it.

633
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:00,500
 She said, I'd be honored to fundraise for you.

634
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:03,060
 But she said, I want to be really honest about something.

635
00:25:03,060 --> 00:25:05,740
 She said, I believe Christianity is for the weak.

636
00:25:05,740 --> 00:25:08,420
 I just want to be upfront about it.

637
00:25:08,420 --> 00:25:12,920
 And I said, wow, I'm so glad you understand it.

638
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:19,320
 And she said, come again?

639
00:25:20,340 --> 00:25:22,060
 I said, you nailed it.

640
00:25:22,060 --> 00:25:25,140
 Christianity is for the weak.

641
00:25:25,140 --> 00:25:29,620
 And you're looking at one of the weakest of them all.

642
00:25:29,620 --> 00:25:31,940
 Where would I be but for the grace of God?

643
00:25:31,940 --> 00:25:33,780
 Where would I be?

644
00:25:33,780 --> 00:25:35,740
 It's not my crutch, it's my wheelchair, man.

645
00:25:35,740 --> 00:25:36,860
 It's my stretcher.

646
00:25:36,860 --> 00:25:39,220
 I've only got Jesus.

647
00:25:39,220 --> 00:25:43,740
 And Jesus got me when I needed Jesus most.

648
00:25:43,740 --> 00:25:45,660
 When I was raging against the world

649
00:25:45,660 --> 00:25:47,500
 and the world was raging against me,

650
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:50,440
 and I said, do I even matter, and is God even real,

651
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:52,860
 and does he even care?

652
00:25:52,860 --> 00:25:56,780
 And I encountered a God who indeed was real and did care.

653
00:25:56,780 --> 00:26:01,340
 And I remember she sent an email right that night.

654
00:26:01,340 --> 00:26:02,940
 She said, I didn't mean to call you weak.

655
00:26:02,940 --> 00:26:04,780
 I wasn't trying to insult you.

656
00:26:04,780 --> 00:26:06,580
 I said, no, you nailed it.

657
00:26:06,580 --> 00:26:07,580
 You got it.

658
00:26:07,580 --> 00:26:09,260
 Sleep tight, don't worry.

659
00:26:09,260 --> 00:26:12,460
 I don't mean I'm not weak on the basketball court,

660
00:26:12,460 --> 00:26:15,020
 but I mean in general, I'm, you know.

661
00:26:15,020 --> 00:26:16,620
 And back and forth, this flurry of games.

662
00:26:16,620 --> 00:26:18,500
 And finally she said, look, could we meet for coffee?

663
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:20,780
 And she had been raised by high power lawyers.

664
00:26:20,780 --> 00:26:22,500
 She's mayor of the city council.

665
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:23,340
 You know, she's got like,

666
00:26:23,340 --> 00:26:25,860
 she's running a whole program at the school.

667
00:26:25,860 --> 00:26:28,940
 She's just like, all she knows is strength and projection

668
00:26:28,940 --> 00:26:30,920
 and like, you know, champion and victory.

669
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:32,760
 And she meets me for coffee in this coffee shop

670
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:34,460
 and she goes to say hi,

671
00:26:34,460 --> 00:26:35,980
 but instead she just starts weeping.

672
00:26:35,980 --> 00:26:37,780
 She says, I'm so weak.

673
00:26:37,780 --> 00:26:40,780
 I'm so weak.

674
00:26:40,780 --> 00:26:43,300
 I'm like, oh, thank God.

675
00:26:43,300 --> 00:26:46,340
 Can we just get to the end of ourselves?

676
00:26:47,180 --> 00:26:49,380
 Could we just get to the end of ourselves

677
00:26:49,380 --> 00:26:50,860
 and the start of God?

678
00:26:50,860 --> 00:26:51,700
 I'm so weak.

679
00:26:51,700 --> 00:26:52,740
 Does God even care?

680
00:26:52,740 --> 00:26:53,860
 Is this even real?

681
00:26:53,860 --> 00:26:58,420
 Could we just be real and honest?

682
00:26:58,420 --> 00:27:00,620
 You know, it's really interesting.

683
00:27:00,620 --> 00:27:02,780
 I love, part of the thing I love about the story

684
00:27:02,780 --> 00:27:05,020
 is that Jesus does not rebuke their question.

685
00:27:05,020 --> 00:27:07,400
 He responds.

686
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:10,260
 He doesn't respond with words.

687
00:27:10,260 --> 00:27:13,260
 He responds with presence, with action.

688
00:27:13,260 --> 00:27:16,260
 He responds to their need, their deepest concern.

689
00:27:16,260 --> 00:27:18,900
 Do you even care if we drown?

690
00:27:18,900 --> 00:27:20,960
 Jesus is like, watch this.

691
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:23,540
 And responds.

692
00:27:23,540 --> 00:27:27,260
 Quiet, be still, he says to the sea.

693
00:27:27,260 --> 00:27:31,820
 Quiet, be still.

694
00:27:31,820 --> 00:27:34,800
 Jesus cares.

695
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:37,980
 That's the answer to their question.

696
00:27:37,980 --> 00:27:41,220
 Not in a theological textbook, not in a teaching time,

697
00:27:41,220 --> 00:27:43,540
 in the middle of the storms of the boat,

698
00:27:43,540 --> 00:27:45,980
 you know, where David even says, you know,

699
00:27:45,980 --> 00:27:48,300
 I finally figured out if I get to the top

700
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:51,140
 of the glorious heavens, there God is.

701
00:27:51,140 --> 00:27:56,140
 And if I make my bed in the depths of hell, there God is.

702
00:27:56,140 --> 00:27:59,040
 Does he care?

703
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:02,560
 He responds.

704
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:06,640
 And Jesus answers with two questions.

705
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:11,260
 Do you know that Jesus asked over 323 questions

706
00:28:11,260 --> 00:28:13,660
 in the gospels, if you add them all up?

707
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:17,820
 He was asked 189 and he only answered directly three.

708
00:28:17,820 --> 00:28:23,820
 So convicted as a Christian leader, you know,

709
00:28:23,820 --> 00:28:25,140
 where you come to this place and all we do

710
00:28:25,140 --> 00:28:27,660
 is give people answers, and all Jesus did

711
00:28:27,660 --> 00:28:29,100
 was give people questions.

712
00:28:29,100 --> 00:28:35,340
 And the two questions that he says are this.

713
00:28:35,340 --> 00:28:36,600
 Why are you so afraid?

714
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:41,140
 Now, I used to read the questions of Jesus

715
00:28:41,140 --> 00:28:45,780
 like sarcastic rebuttals, you know?

716
00:28:45,780 --> 00:28:47,180
 Like, why are you so afraid?

717
00:28:47,180 --> 00:28:49,880
 Where's your faith?

718
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:53,260
 And then like I progressed to like Jesus

719
00:28:53,260 --> 00:28:55,540
 more like passive aggressive, like my mom,

720
00:28:55,540 --> 00:28:56,980
 like are you gonna wear that?

721
00:28:56,980 --> 00:29:03,060
 Right, passive aggressive, we're asking questions,

722
00:29:03,060 --> 00:29:05,220
 but really we're just like trying to say the thing,

723
00:29:05,220 --> 00:29:06,820
 you know?

724
00:29:06,820 --> 00:29:08,420
 And then I actually thought, you know what,

725
00:29:08,420 --> 00:29:13,420
 I think I might just, I might just actually assume

726
00:29:13,420 --> 00:29:16,680
 that Jesus is really asking genuine questions.

727
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:21,260
 What if Jesus is really wanting to know?

728
00:29:21,260 --> 00:29:23,420
 What if they're like legitimate questions?

729
00:29:23,420 --> 00:29:26,480
 This is a really great, I spent years just printing off

730
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:29,900
 all the questions of Jesus and asking them.

731
00:29:29,900 --> 00:29:31,180
 They're amazing.

732
00:29:31,180 --> 00:29:33,280
 Like questions like, do you wanna be well?

733
00:29:33,280 --> 00:29:37,280
 I just spent a week of my life letting Jesus ask me,

734
00:29:37,280 --> 00:29:38,480
 do you wanna be well?

735
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:41,620
 Do you wanna be well?

736
00:29:41,620 --> 00:29:43,660
 These questions, why are you so afraid?

737
00:29:43,660 --> 00:29:48,300
 I think he genuinely wants to know, why are you so afraid?

738
00:29:48,300 --> 00:29:53,020
 Fear is the currency of oppression.

739
00:29:53,020 --> 00:29:55,740
 You know, fear is, it's a currency, so you get caught up.

740
00:29:55,740 --> 00:29:58,660
 So if fear is motivating you, whatever your decision is,

741
00:29:58,660 --> 00:30:00,220
 you will either be oppressed

742
00:30:00,220 --> 00:30:02,780
 or you'll be oppressing somebody else.

743
00:30:02,780 --> 00:30:05,820
 If fear is your motivator, it will get you into a currency.

744
00:30:05,820 --> 00:30:07,020
 That's how oppression works.

745
00:30:07,020 --> 00:30:08,660
 Its currency is fear.

746
00:30:08,660 --> 00:30:12,660
 And we live in a currency of fear.

747
00:30:12,660 --> 00:30:16,020
 I mean, all around the world, we've never been so afraid.

748
00:30:16,020 --> 00:30:18,880
 And I feel like part of the formation, the resistance,

749
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,720
 when Jesus invites us to go with him,

750
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:22,120
 which is what discipleship is,

751
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:23,520
 to cross over to the other side,

752
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:26,160
 to respond to the cry of the world,

753
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:31,320
 one of the questions he asks us is, why are we so afraid?

754
00:30:31,320 --> 00:30:33,280
 And it's a good question.

755
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:35,800
 Because you can't deal with fear

756
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:39,640
 if you're not willing to name the fear, right?

757
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:43,040
 You can't deal with fear by denying fear.

758
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:45,400
 You can't deal with fear by like putting up the,

759
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:47,000
 I am not afraid, I am not afraid,

760
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,300
 and saying it 10 times a day

761
00:30:48,300 --> 00:30:50,000
 so that finally you're not afraid.

762
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:54,320
 You gotta deal with fear by actually naming the fear

763
00:30:54,320 --> 00:30:57,400
 and then inviting a power greater than the fear,

764
00:30:57,400 --> 00:30:58,760
 which the scripture is very clear.

765
00:30:58,760 --> 00:31:00,600
 The power greater than the fear is perfect love,

766
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:03,100
 and perfect love is a person of Jesus.

767
00:31:03,100 --> 00:31:06,980
 And Jesus is with them, and he says, why are you so afraid?

768
00:31:06,980 --> 00:31:09,700
 And when you really get honest with this,

769
00:31:09,700 --> 00:31:10,940
 I mean, why are you so afraid?

770
00:31:10,940 --> 00:31:13,380
 I mean, what are you afraid of?

771
00:31:13,380 --> 00:31:15,220
 When Jesus is inviting you to cross over,

772
00:31:15,220 --> 00:31:16,820
 when Jesus is disrupting your life,

773
00:31:16,820 --> 00:31:17,660
 what are we afraid of?

774
00:31:17,660 --> 00:31:19,420
 We're afraid of looking like fools.

775
00:31:19,420 --> 00:31:20,940
 We're afraid of losing favor, maybe.

776
00:31:20,940 --> 00:31:22,820
 I'm afraid of failing.

777
00:31:22,820 --> 00:31:23,940
 I'm terrified of failing.

778
00:31:23,940 --> 00:31:25,140
 Maybe I'll say the wrong thing.

779
00:31:25,140 --> 00:31:26,260
 Maybe I'll say the right thing.

780
00:31:26,260 --> 00:31:27,100
 I don't know.

781
00:31:27,100 --> 00:31:27,920
 Maybe people will love me.

782
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:29,180
 Maybe people will hate me.

783
00:31:29,180 --> 00:31:30,540
 I mean, the fears are endless,

784
00:31:30,540 --> 00:31:31,860
 but getting honest with the fear,

785
00:31:31,860 --> 00:31:33,180
 why are you so afraid?

786
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:36,900
 And then realizing, ah, in the middle of my fear,

787
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:39,820
 here is one who is perfect love,

788
00:31:39,820 --> 00:31:42,960
 who can drive it out, who can drive it out.

789
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:45,740
 And the second question, in the NIV,

790
00:31:45,740 --> 00:31:47,300
 it puts it in a weird way.

791
00:31:47,300 --> 00:31:48,860
 It says, the one that we just read,

792
00:31:48,860 --> 00:31:50,980
 it says, have you no faith?

793
00:31:50,980 --> 00:31:54,080
 The question really in the text is, where is your faith?

794
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:56,500
 They obviously have faith.

795
00:31:56,500 --> 00:31:57,660
 They're in the boat with Jesus.

796
00:31:57,660 --> 00:31:58,820
 They're going to the other side.

797
00:31:58,820 --> 00:32:00,060
 Three cheers for the disciples.

798
00:32:00,060 --> 00:32:00,900
 They did it.

799
00:32:00,900 --> 00:32:01,740
 You know, they're doing it.

800
00:32:01,740 --> 00:32:03,860
 They're on the journey.

801
00:32:03,860 --> 00:32:05,180
 And again, just for the record,

802
00:32:05,180 --> 00:32:07,140
 the journey is the point.

803
00:32:07,140 --> 00:32:10,340
 To be like Jesus is the point.

804
00:32:10,340 --> 00:32:12,780
 We're always constantly, once I get to the other side,

805
00:32:12,780 --> 00:32:13,620
 that'll be the point.

806
00:32:13,620 --> 00:32:16,580
 No, the point is to encounter Jesus,

807
00:32:16,580 --> 00:32:19,180
 to be with Jesus, to be honest with Jesus,

808
00:32:19,180 --> 00:32:20,780
 to ask the questions of Jesus,

809
00:32:20,780 --> 00:32:22,060
 to have an encounter with Jesus.

810
00:32:22,060 --> 00:32:23,040
 That is the point.

811
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:24,580
 They're living the point.

812
00:32:24,580 --> 00:32:29,360
 And he says, where is your faith?

813
00:32:29,360 --> 00:32:31,120
 I love it.

814
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:32,020
 Where is your faith?

815
00:32:32,020 --> 00:32:36,340
 I would imagine, I mean, I'm just making this up,

816
00:32:36,340 --> 00:32:37,900
 but I'd imagine some of their faith

817
00:32:37,900 --> 00:32:39,940
 might have been in their own ability.

818
00:32:39,940 --> 00:32:40,840
 They're sailors.

819
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:44,800
 They've crossed that sea a bunch of times.

820
00:32:44,800 --> 00:32:46,740
 I mean, part of their faith

821
00:32:46,740 --> 00:32:47,820
 might have been in their own ability,

822
00:32:47,820 --> 00:32:49,100
 and they're getting to the end of that

823
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:51,080
 in a real quick hurry.

824
00:32:51,080 --> 00:32:52,620
 Which, by the way, the end of yourself

825
00:32:52,620 --> 00:32:53,620
 is the beginning of God.

826
00:32:53,620 --> 00:32:55,480
 It's a beautiful place to get to.

827
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:57,460
 The sweet surrender of getting to the end

828
00:32:57,460 --> 00:32:59,180
 of your own capacity, where you realize

829
00:32:59,180 --> 00:33:00,780
 the faith that you had in these things,

830
00:33:00,780 --> 00:33:03,340
 even your own things, are not gonna get you there.

831
00:33:03,340 --> 00:33:08,320
 You're gonna need to put your faith in something real.

832
00:33:08,320 --> 00:33:11,340
 Where is your faith?

833
00:33:11,340 --> 00:33:16,540
 You know, it's not about quantity faith, right?

834
00:33:16,540 --> 00:33:17,380
 Jesus told us this.

835
00:33:17,380 --> 00:33:18,580
 It's just like a mustard seed,

836
00:33:18,580 --> 00:33:20,580
 you just need a tiny little bit.

837
00:33:20,580 --> 00:33:23,380
 But locating it and putting that faith

838
00:33:23,380 --> 00:33:26,900
 in the one who is faithful, that's a work.

839
00:33:26,900 --> 00:33:28,740
 That's a work.

840
00:33:28,740 --> 00:33:29,700
 That's a work of discipleship.

841
00:33:29,700 --> 00:33:30,740
 Locating your faith.

842
00:33:30,740 --> 00:33:31,580
 Where is your faith?

843
00:33:31,580 --> 00:33:34,340
 Is your faith in a political system or an outcome?

844
00:33:34,340 --> 00:33:36,820
 Is your faith in your church's ability to do something?

845
00:33:36,820 --> 00:33:39,700
 Is your faith in your economic outcome?

846
00:33:39,700 --> 00:33:41,160
 Is your faith in the possibility

847
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:42,340
 of what it will look like?

848
00:33:42,340 --> 00:33:43,660
 Where is your faith?

849
00:33:43,660 --> 00:33:48,100
 And if you could find your faith

850
00:33:48,100 --> 00:33:52,420
 and put it, redirect it, into the person of Jesus,

851
00:33:52,420 --> 00:33:54,660
 you will be encountering the one

852
00:33:54,660 --> 00:33:56,500
 who could drive out the fear,

853
00:33:56,500 --> 00:33:58,900
 who could answer some of your deepest questions.

854
00:33:59,740 --> 00:34:02,740
 And could help you reimagine a life

855
00:34:02,740 --> 00:34:07,740
 that is full of the promises and the purposes of God.

856
00:34:07,740 --> 00:34:12,220
 I was sharing about this camp I was at.

857
00:34:12,220 --> 00:34:15,620
 It was this really religious, boring camp as a kid.

858
00:34:15,620 --> 00:34:16,540
 A music camp.

859
00:34:16,540 --> 00:34:18,620
 It was literally, it was you snooze, you win.

860
00:34:18,620 --> 00:34:20,500
 That's what I called it.

861
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:21,900
 And I was there, they invited me to come.

862
00:34:21,900 --> 00:34:24,780
 It's like the Bible teacher, I was like, ooh.

863
00:34:24,780 --> 00:34:27,020
 And I went anyway, and it was a disruption.

864
00:34:27,020 --> 00:34:30,060
 And in the middle of this camp, Jesus showed up.

865
00:34:30,060 --> 00:34:31,060
 I can't even describe it.

866
00:34:31,060 --> 00:34:33,340
 It was like the craziest thing I've ever seen.

867
00:34:33,340 --> 00:34:35,500
 The only thing I could think is the drier the wood,

868
00:34:35,500 --> 00:34:38,580
 the light, the bigger the fire, right?

869
00:34:38,580 --> 00:34:40,100
 And God just showed up,

870
00:34:40,100 --> 00:34:42,500
 and these kids just started encountering Jesus.

871
00:34:42,500 --> 00:34:46,060
 And I remember this one kid was describing what had happened

872
00:34:46,060 --> 00:34:48,320
 and it was a testimony night, and he grabbed this mic.

873
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:50,280
 It's a very religious crowd, he just grabs this mic,

874
00:34:50,280 --> 00:34:52,220
 and he goes, "I just, the other week,"

875
00:34:52,220 --> 00:34:54,260
 he said, "I was at university, and I just like,

876
00:34:54,260 --> 00:34:56,240
 "I looked up to heaven and I raised my fist

877
00:34:56,240 --> 00:34:59,940
 "and I gave God the finger, I said, 'F you God!'"

878
00:34:59,940 --> 00:35:01,300
 Except he didn't say, "F you God."

879
00:35:01,300 --> 00:35:03,500
 I'm like giving you a sanitized version.

880
00:35:03,500 --> 00:35:05,340
 He's just like, "F you God!"

881
00:35:05,340 --> 00:35:07,340
 It's just like, everyone's like, "Ooh!"

882
00:35:07,340 --> 00:35:10,500
 And then the guy just falls to the ground

883
00:35:10,500 --> 00:35:12,820
 and he starts to weep and weep.

884
00:35:12,820 --> 00:35:15,300
 And he said, "I didn't know he was real.

885
00:35:15,300 --> 00:35:18,960
 "I didn't know he was real.

886
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:22,140
 "I didn't know he was real."

887
00:35:22,140 --> 00:35:25,100
 You just feel the spirit break out across the room.

888
00:35:25,100 --> 00:35:26,860
 "I didn't know he was real.

889
00:35:26,860 --> 00:35:30,040
 "He's real."

890
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:34,740
 And it's the final question of the,

891
00:35:34,740 --> 00:35:36,980
 the final question, or it's just love.

892
00:35:36,980 --> 00:35:38,580
 It's like the state of discipleship

893
00:35:38,580 --> 00:35:40,060
 for the rest of your life, you know?

894
00:35:40,060 --> 00:35:42,200
 It's not like you ever arrive.

895
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:44,640
 The disciples, in response to this encounter

896
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:47,520
 where they've witnessed Jesus, respond to them

897
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:50,840
 in care and compassion and strength and power.

898
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:53,260
 He's with them, not against them, he's for them.

899
00:35:53,260 --> 00:35:56,420
 And they get honest and they get past the shallow ideas

900
00:35:56,420 --> 00:35:58,580
 of like pretense and what should be.

901
00:35:58,580 --> 00:36:00,060
 And Jesus is challenging them,

902
00:36:00,060 --> 00:36:01,780
 but in ways that are beautiful.

903
00:36:01,780 --> 00:36:03,840
 'Cause they can start to identify their fear

904
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:05,500
 and they can start to get honest about it

905
00:36:05,500 --> 00:36:07,260
 and they can start to locate their faith.

906
00:36:07,260 --> 00:36:09,380
 And then they just talk amongst themselves

907
00:36:09,380 --> 00:36:11,460
 and they're like, "Who is this guy?

908
00:36:11,460 --> 00:36:14,680
 "Who is this guy?

909
00:36:14,680 --> 00:36:18,340
 "Holy.

910
00:36:18,340 --> 00:36:22,220
 "Who is this guy?

911
00:36:23,220 --> 00:36:25,660
 "Oh, this?

912
00:36:25,660 --> 00:36:27,980
 "This, this?"

913
00:36:27,980 --> 00:36:30,940
 You know, we had a home group at my house.

914
00:36:30,940 --> 00:36:33,700
 I lived in Toronto and a lot of refugees.

915
00:36:33,700 --> 00:36:35,720
 We had a lot of refugee friends and they came over

916
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:38,740
 and we just had this like, it was mediocre food

917
00:36:38,740 --> 00:36:40,460
 most of the time 'cause I was cooking

918
00:36:40,460 --> 00:36:42,620
 'til I wised up and got some of my friends to cook.

919
00:36:42,620 --> 00:36:44,900
 But anyway, we just, but we just,

920
00:36:44,900 --> 00:36:46,380
 there was enough for everybody and we loved each other.

921
00:36:46,380 --> 00:36:48,100
 We welcomed each other and we had this,

922
00:36:48,100 --> 00:36:52,300
 a friend of mine came who is a recent refugee from Sudan

923
00:36:52,300 --> 00:36:55,140
 and she joined us and we're a couple weeks into this thing.

924
00:36:55,140 --> 00:36:56,220
 She just kept coming back.

925
00:36:56,220 --> 00:36:58,020
 You know, I met her through the food bank at our church

926
00:36:58,020 --> 00:36:59,900
 and we're doing dishes in the kitchen

927
00:36:59,900 --> 00:37:03,060
 and she's, I'm passing her a dish

928
00:37:03,060 --> 00:37:06,320
 and she looks at me and she goes, "What is this?"

929
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:09,920
 And I said, "That's a dish."

930
00:37:09,920 --> 00:37:12,220
 She goes, "No, not this."

931
00:37:12,220 --> 00:37:14,000
 She said, "What's this?"

932
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:16,540
 I said, "Oh, this.

933
00:37:16,620 --> 00:37:21,620
 "Oh, this is, this is like people who follow Jesus.

934
00:37:21,620 --> 00:37:23,480
 "Like this is like a family.

935
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:24,660
 "This is like a community.

936
00:37:24,660 --> 00:37:28,080
 "Like this is a place where we all love

937
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:29,580
 "and serve and follow Jesus

938
00:37:29,580 --> 00:37:31,160
 "and like people are welcome here."

939
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:32,940
 And she goes, "This is, but you,"

940
00:37:32,940 --> 00:37:35,120
 she said to me, "But I'm a Muslim."

941
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:38,100
 I said, "Oh, are you?"

942
00:37:38,100 --> 00:37:39,400
 She said, "Yeah."

943
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:41,480
 So like, "Should I leave?"

944
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:44,660
 I said, "No, I love you double now."

945
00:37:45,900 --> 00:37:46,760
 She goes, "No, like why would you leave?

946
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:47,600
 "I don't care.

947
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:48,420
 "I didn't know you were,"

948
00:37:48,420 --> 00:37:49,260
 she's like, "I know you didn't know,

949
00:37:49,260 --> 00:37:50,340
 "but like I've been keeping it a secret.

950
00:37:50,340 --> 00:37:51,180
 "Like should I?"

951
00:37:51,180 --> 00:37:53,680
 And I said, "No, like it's all good, man.

952
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:54,520
 "Are you okay?

953
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:55,340
 "Like is the food okay?

954
00:37:55,340 --> 00:37:56,180
 "Like should I change the food

955
00:37:56,180 --> 00:37:57,120
 "so that you're more comfortable?

956
00:37:57,120 --> 00:37:58,220
 "Like what do you need?"

957
00:37:58,220 --> 00:38:01,260
 She goes, "No, like I just didn't think I would be welcome."

958
00:38:01,260 --> 00:38:02,520
 And we're on this couple of weeks later.

959
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:03,360
 She looks at me and she goes,

960
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:06,400
 "Okay, what is this exactly again?"

961
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:10,580
 And in the end, the only answer I had for her in the end,

962
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:12,440
 the only answer I had for her was,

963
00:38:12,440 --> 00:38:15,200
 "This is, this is Jesus."

964
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:17,440
 This is Jesus.

965
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:21,360
 This person who heard your cry

966
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:23,840
 in this like little tiny apartment that you're stuck in

967
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:25,000
 on the other side of the world

968
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:26,720
 because you're fleeing for your life

969
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:28,160
 and you're fleeing from persecution

970
00:38:28,160 --> 00:38:31,320
 and you feel paranoid about everybody and unwelcome

971
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:33,840
 and you feel unknown and you feel unloved.

972
00:38:33,840 --> 00:38:35,680
 This is the Jesus who heard the cry

973
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:38,000
 and brought you to a people to help tell you

974
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,200
 that you're not alone and that you are beloved

975
00:38:40,200 --> 00:38:43,320
 and that God sees all the way through your worst questions

976
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:45,840
 and your hardest answers and all of your fears

977
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:47,360
 and all of your concerns

978
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:50,200
 and actually even sees the faith that you have

979
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:52,200
 to want something real for your life.

980
00:38:52,200 --> 00:38:53,160
 This is Jesus.

981
00:38:53,160 --> 00:38:54,960
 And she said, "I'll have all of him.

982
00:38:54,960 --> 00:38:57,880
 "I'll have all of him.

983
00:38:57,880 --> 00:39:01,000
 "I'll have all of him."

984
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:01,840
 Who wouldn't?

985
00:39:01,840 --> 00:39:03,560
 Huh?

986
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:05,240
 Who wouldn't?

987
00:39:05,240 --> 00:39:07,880
 If they could only know,

988
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:10,880
 if they could only see the invitation,

989
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:11,840
 if you could only see,

990
00:39:11,840 --> 00:39:13,880
 maybe you're here and you just thought Christianity

991
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:15,040
 was just a belief system,

992
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:17,960
 like we're in competition with other religions of the world.

993
00:39:17,960 --> 00:39:18,880
 (laughs)

994
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:20,400
 That's not what it is.

995
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:24,960
 Christianity is an invitation,

996
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:26,760
 a disruption to the status quo

997
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:30,480
 to reimagine our lives in a world

998
00:39:30,480 --> 00:39:32,260
 where things are as they should be,

999
00:39:32,260 --> 00:39:33,480
 where there's more than enough,

1000
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:35,040
 where the lonely are put in families,

1001
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:36,480
 where there are gardens and wilderness,

1002
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:39,120
 where there's a people who lay down arms

1003
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:40,080
 and love each other,

1004
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:44,600
 a place where the grace of God is so radically inclusive

1005
00:39:44,600 --> 00:39:46,500
 that it doesn't matter what your background is

1006
00:39:46,500 --> 00:39:47,440
 or what your sin is.

1007
00:39:47,440 --> 00:39:49,920
 You could even be a demonically possessed guy

1008
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:51,760
 living with pigs.

1009
00:39:51,760 --> 00:39:56,160
 And Jesus would move heaven and earth to get to you

1010
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:58,600
 and liberate you

1011
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:01,660
 and love you.

1012
00:40:01,660 --> 00:40:05,580
 Who is this man?

1013
00:40:05,580 --> 00:40:09,320
 It's Jesus.

1014
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:11,320
 It's Jesus.

1015
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:16,600
 My friend who became the mayor in the end,

1016
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:19,920
 not only a follower of Jesus, but became a mayor,

1017
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:22,800
 and the town had such a horrible history

1018
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:26,040
 of violence against indigenous Canadians,

1019
00:40:26,040 --> 00:40:27,800
 just a lot of injustice.

1020
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:33,400
 And she had been so transformed by Jesus

1021
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:38,000
 that she went from this strong powerhouse lawyer person

1022
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:40,800
 to this like weeping, weak,

1023
00:40:40,800 --> 00:40:45,980
 like fully alive, but also emotionally tapped in person.

1024
00:40:45,980 --> 00:40:47,880
 And she would just sit in city council

1025
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:50,440
 and weep and weep and weep.

1026
00:40:50,440 --> 00:40:52,360
 And she started a prayer meeting

1027
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:54,960
 in the city hall of repentance and lament

1028
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:56,360
 for the violence that had been done

1029
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:57,760
 to the indigenous community.

1030
00:40:57,760 --> 00:41:02,400
 And a revival and a reconciliation began to start

1031
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:04,800
 at the center of that town.

1032
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:07,680
 Not because of her strength, but because of her weakness,

1033
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:09,840
 but because of her weakness being found

1034
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:13,160
 in the person of Jesus, because she got honest,

1035
00:41:13,160 --> 00:41:15,480
 because she came, because she had a genuine encounter,

1036
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:17,400
 because she heard the cry,

1037
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:19,860
 because the spirit of God was in her hearing the cry,

1038
00:41:19,860 --> 00:41:22,920
 because she saw the disruption and went to the other side.

1039
00:41:22,920 --> 00:41:26,720
 And transformation happens.

1040
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:31,720
 Don't you want, don't you want that kind of encounter

1041
00:41:31,720 --> 00:41:36,880
 with Jesus and live that kind of life?

1042
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:39,040
 (silence)

1043
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:43,260
 Yeah, let's pray.

1044
00:41:43,260 --> 00:41:55,480
 You know, I, just before we pray,

1045
00:41:55,480 --> 00:42:02,000
 I feel like telling you my son Judah

1046
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:04,160
 was really late learning to ride a bike.

1047
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:08,200
 He was really careful, he had these training wheels on.

1048
00:42:08,200 --> 00:42:09,760
 He didn't want to leave them.

1049
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:11,960
 He just, I'll be fine, you know?

1050
00:42:11,960 --> 00:42:13,720
 And he's like way too old for this.

1051
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:16,520
 Like a little girl biked by him without the training wheels.

1052
00:42:16,520 --> 00:42:18,700
 I was like, I can't take this anymore.

1053
00:42:18,700 --> 00:42:21,480
 So I said to him, honey, let's just try it one time.

1054
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:22,940
 We'll just put the training wheels up.

1055
00:42:22,940 --> 00:42:24,120
 We won't take them off the bike.

1056
00:42:24,120 --> 00:42:26,440
 We'll just put them up and give it a try.

1057
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:27,280
 And if it doesn't work,

1058
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:28,660
 we'll put the training wheels back down.

1059
00:42:28,660 --> 00:42:31,160
 Like just, and he goes, okay, I'll give it a try.

1060
00:42:31,160 --> 00:42:33,520
 And of course he just takes off.

1061
00:42:33,520 --> 00:42:34,520
 He's more than ready.

1062
00:42:34,520 --> 00:42:36,720
 And he comes back and he's just all smiles.

1063
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:39,960
 And he looks at me, he goes, mom, I'm totally riding a bike.

1064
00:42:39,960 --> 00:42:41,400
 And I said, I know, honey, I saw it.

1065
00:42:41,400 --> 00:42:42,240
 I'm so proud of you.

1066
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:46,100
 And he said to me, mom, you could totally preach this.

1067
00:42:46,100 --> 00:42:51,760
 I said, thanks.

1068
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:54,640
 And what do you mean?

1069
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:56,400
 And he goes, just think about it.

1070
00:42:56,400 --> 00:43:01,440
 My training wheels were holding me back.

1071
00:43:01,440 --> 00:43:03,680
 (exhaling)

1072
00:43:03,680 --> 00:43:08,720
 God, we confess.

1073
00:43:08,720 --> 00:43:11,640
 We confess that we're so afraid.

1074
00:43:11,640 --> 00:43:17,060
 We have training wheels on training wheels on training wheels

1075
00:43:17,060 --> 00:43:21,040
 'cause we're so scared of falling or failing or,

1076
00:43:21,040 --> 00:43:23,620
 I don't know, all of us.

1077
00:43:23,620 --> 00:43:27,520
 We have deep questions that we've never even,

1078
00:43:27,520 --> 00:43:31,260
 we've never even had the strength to ask.

1079
00:43:31,260 --> 00:43:33,040
 We don't even know if it's okay, but

1080
00:43:33,040 --> 00:43:39,080
 would you help us be real and to be brave

1081
00:43:39,080 --> 00:43:42,560
 and to be honest and to be real?

1082
00:43:42,560 --> 00:43:47,560
 Would you help us to understand that the disruption

1083
00:43:47,560 --> 00:43:50,960
 is really an invitation from heaven to reimagine a world

1084
00:43:50,960 --> 00:43:55,860
 and a life that is alive with you?

1085
00:43:55,860 --> 00:44:01,080
 And I don't know what it is.

1086
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:03,220
 I feel like there are people here who just need

1087
00:44:03,220 --> 00:44:06,660
 to trust Jesus to take the training wheels off.

1088
00:44:06,660 --> 00:44:09,600
 And I also just wanna say, if you're here

1089
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:11,280
 and you actually thought Christianity

1090
00:44:11,280 --> 00:44:13,000
 was like some religious belief system

1091
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:15,420
 and not an actual come and follow me

1092
00:44:15,420 --> 00:44:18,040
 from a person who is alive and inviting you

1093
00:44:18,040 --> 00:44:21,660
 to come alive in the person of Jesus,

1094
00:44:21,660 --> 00:44:23,220
 then this is your moment.

1095
00:44:23,220 --> 00:44:27,140
 You are, all you need to do is just say I'm in.

1096
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:28,820
 Take the invitation.

1097
00:44:28,820 --> 00:44:29,660
 I'm coming.

1098
00:44:29,660 --> 00:44:31,260
 I'm belonging.

1099
00:44:31,260 --> 00:44:32,660
 You know, my friend from Sudan,

1100
00:44:32,660 --> 00:44:33,960
 she's just like I'm not leaving.

1101
00:44:33,960 --> 00:44:34,800
 I'm coming.

1102
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:36,740
 I want all there is and she's still doing it.

1103
00:44:36,740 --> 00:44:41,100
 She's still doing it, experiencing the boundlessness

1104
00:44:41,100 --> 00:44:43,540
 of reimagining her life with Jesus.

1105
00:44:43,540 --> 00:44:47,180
 That's it, you can do that.

1106
00:44:47,180 --> 00:44:50,060
 Just let someone from this church know so we could help you

1107
00:44:50,060 --> 00:44:51,800
 and we could travel with you and you would know

1108
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:55,200
 that you are welcome and you're not alone, not anymore.

1109
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:57,080
 You are welcome, you belong.

1110
00:44:58,380 --> 00:45:00,980
 You are seen and know God heard your cry.

1111
00:45:00,980 --> 00:45:04,840
 God heard your cry in response.

1112
00:45:04,840 --> 00:45:08,900
 And you may be here and you may be in resistance

1113
00:45:08,900 --> 00:45:10,580
 thinking wow, I must got it wrong

1114
00:45:10,580 --> 00:45:12,540
 'cause if God was with me, this wouldn't be so hard

1115
00:45:12,540 --> 00:45:16,260
 and you just need to be relieved of that false thought.

1116
00:45:16,260 --> 00:45:18,960
 God is with you and it's hard.

1117
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:24,080
 And God's with you and it's hard and God's with you.

1118
00:45:25,100 --> 00:45:30,100
 And it's hard, relax into the training, the journey.

1119
00:45:30,100 --> 00:45:33,760
 God is enough.

1120
00:45:33,760 --> 00:45:38,660
 God is alive, God is here.

1121
00:45:38,660 --> 00:45:40,860
 God is with us.

1122
00:45:40,860 --> 00:45:50,100
 So Jesus, we just say thank you and yes.

1123
00:45:50,100 --> 00:45:54,320
 Thank you for the invitation.

1124
00:45:55,320 --> 00:45:59,020
 To go to the other side and we just say yes.

1125
00:45:59,020 --> 00:46:04,440
 Yes to inconvenience, yes to leaving status quo,

1126
00:46:04,440 --> 00:46:08,800
 yes to yikes, yes to we don't know what we're doing,

1127
00:46:08,800 --> 00:46:11,580
 yes to we might fail, yes to we might come

1128
00:46:11,580 --> 00:46:15,600
 against resistance, yes to the storm if necessary,

1129
00:46:15,600 --> 00:46:18,440
 yes to the one that we're scared of on the other side,

1130
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:22,660
 yes to rejection, yes to pain, yes.

1131
00:46:23,660 --> 00:46:27,680
 Because it's yes to you that we're really saying.

1132
00:46:27,680 --> 00:46:31,340
 So we say it.

1133
00:46:31,340 --> 00:46:36,940
 We say it, even if we tremble, our voices tremble,

1134
00:46:36,940 --> 00:46:39,860
 we say it still, yes.

1135
00:46:39,860 --> 00:46:44,860
 Yes to you, yes to the living one, yes to come up here,

1136
00:46:44,860 --> 00:46:49,220
 come up now and see the holy, holy, holy,

1137
00:46:49,220 --> 00:46:52,980
 slain lamb of God, every tribe, every tongue,

1138
00:46:52,980 --> 00:46:56,820
 every nation, worshiping the one.

1139
00:46:56,820 --> 00:47:00,420
 Yes.

1140
00:47:00,420 --> 00:47:04,960
 Let our lives be yes.

1141
00:47:04,960 --> 00:47:10,060
 We'll go, we'll go to the other side.

1142
00:47:18,940 --> 00:47:21,500
 Just take a minute to imagine yourself in the boat.

1143
00:47:21,500 --> 00:47:29,540
 Maybe you need to imagine yourself on the shore

1144
00:47:29,540 --> 00:47:32,740
 and Jesus' invitation is like, come on, let's go.

1145
00:47:32,740 --> 00:47:38,020
 Maybe you're in the middle of the sea

1146
00:47:38,020 --> 00:47:40,080
 and you're like, what on earth?

1147
00:47:40,080 --> 00:47:43,940
 Ask him.

1148
00:47:43,940 --> 00:47:47,040
 Answer him.

1149
00:47:47,040 --> 00:47:47,880
 Ask him.

1150
00:47:47,880 --> 00:47:52,100
 And be amazed.

1151
00:47:52,100 --> 00:47:58,860
 He's better than you ever imagined.

1152
00:47:58,860 --> 00:48:03,960
 Greater than you could ever even understand.

1153
00:48:03,960 --> 00:48:08,360
 He's truer than your deepest fear.

1154
00:48:15,440 --> 00:48:17,800
 Jesus, we wanna know you, we wanna follow you,

1155
00:48:17,800 --> 00:48:20,040
 we wanna encounter your glory.

1156
00:48:20,040 --> 00:48:22,320
 Thank you.

1157
00:48:22,320 --> 00:48:25,280
 Thank you.

1158
00:48:25,280 --> 00:48:28,040
 (wind whooshing)

1159
00:48:28,040 --> 00:48:30,200
 (silence)

1160
00:48:30,200 --> 00:48:40,200
 [BLANK_AUDIO]

